    "To better suit climate data characteristics through model training, we depended on data normalization and scaling as an important preprocessing step to ensure that the input seven variable are on a similar scale, which can improve the training process and model performance.",
    "We applied Min-Max Scaling to physical climate parameter data which rescaled each variable to a fixed range, typically between 0 and 1.",
    "This is achieved by subtracting the minimum value of the variable and dividing by the difference between the maximum and minimum values, as defined in Eq.",
    "To mitigate computational demands associated with training the proposed model on the entire dataset, we employed a random sampling technique.",
    "This resulted in the creation of a smaller, representative subset of data that maintained balanced representation across all four class types, thereby ensuring training efficiency and generalizability."
